nd distribute are reliable and comply with all CE &amp; international regulations. Our comprehensive warranty illustrates the confidence that we have in our products.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Customers:</b>We focus on our customers\' requirements and are committed to their success.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Distributors:</b>We work closely with our distributors to ensure they provide every customer with the same high quality standards that we insist on with our customers.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>System:</b>We continually maintain and improve the effectiveness of our quality control system. Periodic review of current policies and practices ensure the highest standards for our products and services.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><b>Quality:</b>The manufacturing process is subject to stringent standards of quality assurance. IOPtima products are approved for sale by the regulatory systems in Europe, Israel, China, Canada, Hong Kong, Mexico, Peru, Singapore and Thailand. IOPtima is ISO 13485: 2012 ISO and ISO EN &amp; CAN/CSA 13485: 2003 certified.</span></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"20\" display_desktop=\"true\" display_tablet=\"true\" display_mobile=\"true\"][framed_image image=\"401\" img_size=\"full\" img_link_target=\"_self\" align=\"none\"][spacer height=\"50\" display_desktop=\"true\" display_tablet=\"true\" display_mobile=\"true\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n<script>// <![CDATA[\r\n(function(i,s,o,g,r,a,m){i[\'GoogleAnalyticsObject\']=r;i[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n [r] \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n =i \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n [r] \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n ||function(){ (i \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n [r] \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n .q=i \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n [r] \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n .q||[]).push(arguments)},i \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n\r\n [r] \r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text].l=1*new Date();a=s.createElement(o), m=s.getElementsByTagName(o)[0];a.async=1;a.src=g;m.parentNode.insertBefore(a,m) })(window,document,\'script\',\'//www.google-analytics.com/analytics.js\',\'ga\'); ga(\'create\', \'UA-53735655-1\', \'auto\'); ga(\'send\', \'pageview\');\r\n// ]]></script>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]','Quality','','publish','closed','open','','quality','','','2016-03-24 11:26:28','2016-03-24 11:26:28','',91,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?page_id=56',7,'page','',0),(57,2,'2014-03-27 09:19:00','2014-03-27 09:19:00',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','57','','','2016-07-05 09:38:53','2016-07-05 09:38:53','',91,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?p=57',7,'nav_menu_item','',0),(58,2,'2014-03-27 09:19:00','2014-03-27 09:19:00','','Technology','','publish','closed','closed','','technology','','','2016-07-05 09:38:53','2016-07-05 09:38:53','',0,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?p=58',10,'nav_menu_item','',0),(59,2,'2014-03-27 09:19:00','2014-03-27 09:19:00','','For Physicians','','publish','closed','closed','','for-physicians','','','2016-07-05 09:38:53','2016-07-05 09:38:53','',0,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?p=59',14,'nav_menu_item','',0),(60,2,'2014-03-27 09:18:56','2014-03-27 09:18:56','[vc_row][vc_column align=\"align-center\"][vc_column_text]<iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/qxy3beyQixU?autoplay=1&amp;rel=0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe>[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"35\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Lowering the intraocular pressure (IOP) is the only treatment modality for the management of glaucoma patients, aiming to arrest the irreversible visual field loss. Surgical treatment is usually indicated when the IOP is insufficiently lowered and/or glaucomatous optic neuropathy worsens and visual field defect progresses despite laser Trabeculoplasty or maximally tolerated medical therapy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">CLASS (CO<sub>2</sub> Laser Assisted Sclerectomy Surgery) procedure is similar to trabeculectomy, the major difference being that after the scleral flap is raised, the remaining sclera over the Schelms canal and trabecular meshwork is dissected by the CO2 laser probe until aqueous percolated over the entire dissected bed. The aqueous originated from the unroofed Schlemms canal and juxta-canalicular trabeculum and the dissection stops automatically by the aqueous in the bed and penetration in the AC is avoided. This way the procedure aimed to prevent intra ocular complications.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">The procedure is performed under sub-conjunctival anesthesia. The perilimbal conjunctiva and tenon capsule are dissected. A half-thickness superior fornix-based scleral flap is fashioned with a crescent knife. A red laser aiming beam is used to mark the scanning area boundaries. Scan dimensions (width and length) can be changed within the range of 1 to 4 mm. Initially a wide scan area is used to repeatedly remove layers of sclera until a percolation zone can be readily identified. The CO2 laser is repeatedly applied with time intervals of 2 to 3 seconds between applications to allow percolation to take place and be detected, until sufficient percolation zone of at least 3 mm in region length is clearly evident. The scleral flap is then repositioned and sutured with 10-0 nylon sutures.</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"35\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_message color=\"alert-success\"]\r\n\r\nPeritomy and superficial scleral flap dissection extending to the clear cornea\r\n\r\n[/vc_message][framed_image image=\"580\" style=\"img-rounded\"][spacer height=\"35\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_message color=\"alert-success\"]\r\n\r\nRed aiming beam indicate and confine laser ablation zone distal to the limbus\r\n\r\n[/vc_message][framed_image image=\"581\" style=\"img-rounded\"][spacer height=\"35\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][framed_image image=\"582\" style=\"img-rounded\"][vc_message color=\"alert-success\"]\r\n\r\nLaser ablation aimed at Schlemm\'s canal\r\n\r\n[/vc_message][spacer height=\"40\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][framed_image image=\"583\" style=\"img-rounded\"][vc_message color=\"alert-success\"]\r\n\r\nScleral flap and conjunctiva suturing\r\n\r\n[/vc_message][spacer height=\"40\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]','The Surgical Procedure','','publish','closed','open','','the-surgical-procedure','','','2016-05-14 13:46:38','2016-05-14 13:46:38','',93,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?page_id=60',4,'page','',0),(61,2,'2014-03-27 09:20:20','2014-03-27 09:20:20',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','61','','','2016-07-05 09:38:53','2016-07-05 09:38:53','',93,'http://ioptima.wpengine.com/?p=61',15,'nav_menu_item','',0),(62,2,'2014-03-27 09:19:50','2014-03-27 09:19:50','[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Book Chapters:</h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"20\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][spacer height=\"50\" display_tablet=\"false\" display_mobile=\"false\"][vc_column_text]CO<sub>2</sub> Laser-assisted Deep Sclerectomy Surgery in Samples, John R. Surgical Innovations in Glaucoma. Ed. Iqbal Ike K. Ahmed. Springer 2014, vol XI page 104-106.\r\n\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<a href=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/surgical-innovations-in-glaucoma.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-838 alignleft\" src=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/surgical-innovations-in-glaucoma.jpg\" alt=\"surgical-innovations-in-glaucoma\" width=\"152\" height=\"201\" /></a>[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"50\" display_tablet=\"false\" display_mobile=\"false\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][spacer height=\"50\" display_tablet=\"false\" display_mobile=\"false\"][vc_column_text]Laser-Assisted Techniques for Penetrating and Non-penetrating Glaucoma Surgery in Bettin P, Khaw PT (eds): Glaucoma Surgery. Developments in Ophthalmology. Basel, Karger, 2012, vol 50, pp 96108. [/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<a href=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/256649.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-839 alignleft\" src=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/256649-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"256649\" width=\"153\" height=\"204\" /></a>[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"50\" display_tablet=\"false\" display_mobile=\"false\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"60\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Clinical Publications:</h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"20\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][spacer height=\"50\" display_tablet=\"false\" display_mobile=\"false\"][vc_column_text]Preliminary results of CO<sub>2</sub> laser-assisted sclerectomy surgery (CLASS) in the treatment\r\nof advanced glaucoma in a Chinese population\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]<a href=\"/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/Preliminary-results-of-CO2-laser-assisted-sclerectomy-surgery-CLASS-in-the-treatment-of-advanced-glaucoma-in-a-Chinese-population..pdf\"><img class=\"alignleft wp-image-836 size-thumbnail\" src=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016