age=\"407\" img_size=\"125142\" align=\"right\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text]<i>\"The eye is normally quiet, and vision is maintained soon after surgery. CLASS learning curve is fast. The fluid percolation is titrated during surgery, and further laser applications are provided until a satisfactory clinical result is achieved.</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Prof. Assia Ehud  Meir Medical Center, Kfar Saba, Israel, Inventor</b><b></b>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"30\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][framed_image image=\"403\" align=\"right\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text]<i>\"</i><i>IOPtimas CLASS procedure has true advantages over the Trabeculectomy surgery as it offers an excellent safety profile with an ease of use. It can lower pressure into the lower teens and reduce the patients reliance on glaucoma medications without subjecting the eye to the risks of Trabeculectomy. It also reduces learning curve time for performing deep sclerectomy with very similar results to published data.\"</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Prof. Mermoud Andre - Clinique de Montchoisi, Lausanne, Switzerland</b>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"30\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][framed_image image=\"404\" img_size=\"125  142\" align=\"right\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text]<i>\"In my experience, patient follow up (24 months) demonstrates consistent and sustained IOP lowering. The efficacy and simplicity of the IOPtiMate procedure is remarkable.\"</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. Muoz Gonzalo - Hospital Nisa Valencia al Mar, Valencia, Spain</b>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"30\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][framed_image image=\"406\" img_size=\"125  142\" align=\"right\"][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][vc_column_text]<i>\"From my experience Using IOPtimas CLASS, the procedure is (1) effective in lowering IOP, (2) Easy to use with a short learning curve, (3) high safety profile due to a its laser qualities and (4) reduced post-op recovery and complications associated with other penetrating surgeries.\"</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. Flix Gil Carrasco - Hospital Angeles del Pedreg, Mexico city, Mexico</b>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"30\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text]<img class=\" wp-image-709 alignright\" src=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Dr.-Shoham-Hazon-150x150.jpg\" alt=\"Dr. Shoham-Hazon\" width=\"125\" height=\"125\" />[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][spacer height=\"10\"][vc_column_text]<i>\"There\'s no other glaucoma surgery that maintains the anterior chamber untouched. In standalone case, not even a side port incision is needed. Hence, speedy recovery, no anterior chamber inflammation and least chances of cataract formation. Once you go CLASS you never go TRAB.\"</i>\r\n\r\n<b>Dr. Nir Shoham-Hazon - Barzilai University Hospital, Ashkelon, Israel</b>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column][spacer height=\"30\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<h3>Video Testimonials</h3>\r\n[/vc_column_text][spacer height=\"60\"][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/4\"][vc_column_text]<a href=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/14191743044090.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-852\" src=\"http://ioptima.co.il/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/14191743044090-206x300.jpg\" width=\"125\" height=\"182\" /></a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"3/4\"][spacer height=\"10\"][vc_column_text]<b>Dr. Shlomo Melamed- Chaim Sheba Medical Center Tel Hashomer, Israel</b>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.healio.com/ophthalmology/glaucoma/news/online/%7B1734cfd3-bb9f-4eb7-88ab-c9d37fc2b9a0%7D/surgeon-describes-glaucoma-procedure-using-co2-laser\">Watch Testimonial</a>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column][spacer 